ciscoFcMgmtMIB.name: ciscoFcMgmtMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of Cisco Fibre Channel Management MIB module.

ciscoFcMgmtMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-dwdm@cisco.com
ciscoFcMgmtMIB.description: This module defines management information specific to Fibre Channel-attached devices. This module is an adaptation of IETF's IPS working group's draft, draft-ietf-ips-fcmgmt-mib-02

CfcmFcNameIdOrZero.name: CfcmFcNameIdOrZero
CfcmFcNameIdOrZero.description: The World Wide Name (WWN) associated with a Fibre Channel (FC) entity. WWNs were initially defined as 64-bits in length. The latest definition (for future use) is 128-bits long. The zero-length string value is used in circumstances where the WWN is unassigned/unknown.

CfcmFcAddressId.name: CfcmFcAddressId
CfcmFcAddressId.description: A Fibre Channel Address ID, a 24-bit value unique within the address space of a Fabric.

CfcmDomainIdOrZero.name: CfcmDomainIdOrZero
CfcmDomainIdOrZero.description: The Domain Id (of a FC switch), or zero if no Domain Id has been assigned.

CfcmFcPortType.name: CfcmFcPortType
CfcmFcPortType.description: The type of a Fibre Channel port, being one of the types described below. unknown - Fibre Channel port type is not known. other - the port type is something other than the ones described below. dynamic - the port could be one of the below port types and this varies dynamically. nPort - Any port on a node device, e.g., a disk, PC, etc. that is directly attached to a Fabric port. (Refer FC-PH, FC-FS). nlPort - An 'nPort' that also has arbitrated loop capabilities. (Refer FC-AL-2). fPort - A port on a fibre channel fabric. (Refer FC-PH, FC-FS). flPort - A 'fPort' that also has arbitrated loop capabilities. (Refer FC-AL-2). ePort - A fabric expansion port which attaches to another 'ePort' or 'bPort' to create an Inter-Switch Link. (Refer FC-SW-2). bPort - A bridge port on a device that implements FC-BBW and connects to an E_port on a switch. (Refer FC-BB).

CfcmFcClasses.name: CfcmFcClasses
CfcmFcClasses.description: A set of Fibre Channel classes of service.
CfcmFcClasses.reference: Classes of service are described in FC-FS Section 13.

CfcmFcBbCredit.name: CfcmFcBbCredit
CfcmFcBbCredit.description: The buffer-to-buffer credit of an FC port. i.e., the number of frames a FC device can receive at a time without causing a buffer overrun condition.

CfcmFcBbCreditModel.name: CfcmFcBbCreditModel
CfcmFcBbCreditModel.description: The buffer-to-buffer credit model of an Fx_Port.

CfcmFcDataFieldSize.name: CfcmFcDataFieldSize
CfcmFcDataFieldSize.description: The Receive Data Field Size associated with an FC port.

CfcmFcUnitFunctions.name: CfcmFcUnitFunctions
CfcmFcUnitFunctions.description: A set of functions that a Fibre Channel Interconnect Element or Platform might perform. A value with no bits set, indicates the function(s) are unknown. The individual bits have the following meanings: other - none of the following. hub - a device that interconnects L_Ports, but does not operate as an FL_Port. switch - a fabric element conforming to the Fibre Channel switch fabric set of standards (e.g., FC-SW, FC-SW-2). bridge - a device that encapsulates Fibre Channel frames within another protocol (e.g., FC-BB, FC-BB-2). gateway - a device that converts an FC-4 to another protocol (e.g., FCP to iSCSI). host - a computer system that provides end users services such as computation and storage access. storageSubsys - an integrated collection of storage controllers, storage devices, and necessary software, that provides storage services to one or more hosts. storageAccessDev - a device that provides storage management and access for heterogeneous hosts and heterogeneous devices (e.g., medium changer). nas - a device that connects to a network and provides file access services. wdmux - a device that modulates/demodulates each of several data streams (e.g., Fibre Channel protocol data streams) onto/from a different part of the light spectrum in an optical fiber.

CfcmPhysicalIndexOrZero.name: CfcmPhysicalIndexOrZero
CfcmPhysicalIndexOrZero.description: The index value for a physical entity's row in the Entity MIB's entPhysicalTable. A zero value indicates that no row in the entPhysicalTable is applicable.
CfcmPhysicalIndexOrZero.reference: entPhysicalTable is defined in the Entity MIB, RFC 2737.

CfcmHrSWInstalledIndexOrZero.name: CfcmHrSWInstalledIndexOrZero
CfcmHrSWInstalledIndexOrZero.description: The index value for a software module's row in the Host Resources MIB's hrSWInstalledTable. A zero value indicates that no row in the hrSWInstalledTable is applicable.
CfcmHrSWInstalledIndexOrZero.reference: hrSWInstalledTable is defined in the Host Resources MIB, RFC 2790.

cfcmInstanceTable.name: cfcmInstanceTable
cfcmInstanceTable.description: Information about the local Fibre Channel management instances.

cfcmInstanceEntry.name: cfcmInstanceEntry
cfcmInstanceEntry.description: A list of attributes for a particular local Fibre Channel management instance.

cfcmInstanceIndex.name: cfcmInstanceIndex
cfcmInstanceIndex.description: An arbitrary integer value which uniquely identifies this instance amongst all local Fibre Channel management instances. It is mandatory that this value remain constant between restarts of the agent except, in case of certain re- configurations of the local system where it is natural for it to change. It is desirable that this value remain constant across restarts.

cfcmInstanceWwn.name: cfcmInstanceWwn
cfcmInstanceWwn.description: If the instance has one (or more) WWN(s), then this object contains that (or one of those) WWN(s). If the instance does not have a WWN associated with it, then this object contains the zero-length string.

cfcmInstanceFunctions.name: cfcmInstanceFunctions
cfcmInstanceFunctions.description: One (or more) Fibre Channel unit functions being performed by this instance.

cfcmInstancePhysicalIndex.name: cfcmInstancePhysicalIndex
cfcmInstancePhysicalIndex.reference: entPhysicalIndex is defined in the Entity MIB, RFC 2737.
cfcmInstancePhysicalIndex.description: If this management instance corresponds to a physical component (or to a hierarchy of physical components), then this object's value is the value of the entPhysicalIndex of that component (or of the component at the root of that hierarchy). If there is no correspondence to a physical component (or no component which has an entPhysicalIndex value), then the value of this object is zero.

cfcmInstanceSoftwareIndex.name: cfcmInstanceSoftwareIndex
cfcmInstanceSoftwareIndex.reference: hrSWInstalledIndex is defined in the Host Resources MIB, RFC 2790
cfcmInstanceSoftwareIndex.description: If this management instance corresponds to an installed software module, then this object's value is the value of the hrSWInstalledIndex of that module. If there is no correspondence to an installed software module (or no module which has a hrSWInstalledIndex value), then the value of this object is zero.

cfcmInstanceStatus.name: cfcmInstanceStatus
cfcmInstanceStatus.description: Overall status of the Fibre Channel entity/entities managed by this management instance. The value should reflect the most serious status of such entities.

cfcmInstanceTextName.name: cfcmInstanceTextName
cfcmInstanceTextName.description: A textual name for this management instance and the Fibre Channel entity/entities that it is managing.

cfcmInstanceDescr.name: cfcmInstanceDescr
cfcmInstanceDescr.description: A textual description of this management instance and the Fibre Channel entity/entities that it is managing.

cfcmInstanceFabricId.name: cfcmInstanceFabricId
cfcmInstanceFabricId.description: The globally unique Fabric Identifier which identifies the fabric to which the Fibre Channel entity/entities managed by this management instance are connected, or, of which they are a part. This is typically the Node WWN of the principal switch of a Fibre Channel fabric. The zero-length string indicates that the fabric identifier is unknown (or not applicable).

cfcmSwitchTable.name: cfcmSwitchTable
cfcmSwitchTable.description: A table of information about Fibre Channel switches which are managed by Fibre Channel management instances. Each Fibre Channel management instance can manage one or more Fibre Channel switches.

cfcmSwitchEntry.name: cfcmSwitchEntry
cfcmSwitchEntry.description: Information about a particular Fibre Channel switch which is managed by the management instance given by cfcmInstanceIndex.

cfcmSwitchIndex.name: cfcmSwitchIndex
cfcmSwitchIndex.description: An arbitrary integer which uniquely identifies a Fibre Channel switch amongst those managed by one Fibre Channel management instance.

cfcmSwitchDomainId.name: cfcmSwitchDomainId
cfcmSwitchDomainId.description: The Domain Id of this switch. A value of zero indicates that a switch has not (yet) been assigned a Domain Id.

cfcmSwitchPrincipal.name: cfcmSwitchPrincipal
cfcmSwitchPrincipal.description: An indication of whether this switch is the principal switch within its fabric.

cfcmPortTable.name: cfcmPortTable
cfcmPortTable.reference: RFC 2863, The Interfaces Group MIB, June 2000.
cfcmPortTable.description: Information about Fibre Channel ports. Each Fibre Channel port is represented by one entry in the IF-MIB's ifTable.

cfcmPortEntry.name: cfcmPortEntry
cfcmPortEntry.description: Each entry contains information about a specific port.

cfcmPortInstanceIndex.name: cfcmPortInstanceIndex
cfcmPortInstanceIndex.description: The value of cfcmInstanceIndex by which the Fibre Channel management instance, which manages this port, is identified in the cfcmInstanceTable.

cfcmPortWwn.name: cfcmPortWwn
cfcmPortWwn.description: The World Wide Name of the port, or the zero-length string if the port does not have a WWN.

cfcmPortNodeWwn.name: cfcmPortNodeWwn
cfcmPortNodeWwn.description: The World Wide Name of the Node which contains this port, or the zero-length string if the port does not have a node WWN.

cfcmPortAdminType.name: cfcmPortAdminType
cfcmPortAdminType.description: The administratively desired type of this port. Each port will typically only be able to support a subset of these types.

cfcmPortOperType.name: cfcmPortOperType
cfcmPortOperType.description: The current operational type of this port.

cfcmPortFcCapClass.name: cfcmPortFcCapClass
cfcmPortFcCapClass.description: The classes of service capability of this port.

cfcmPortFcOperClass.name: cfcmPortFcOperClass
cfcmPortFcOperClass.description: The classes of service that are currently operational on this port. For an FL_Port, this is the union of the classes being supported across all attached NL_Ports.

cfcmPortTransmitterType.name: cfcmPortTransmitterType
cfcmPortTransmitterType.description: The technology of the port transceiver.

cfcmPortConnectorType.name: cfcmPortConnectorType
cfcmPortConnectorType.description: The module type of the port connector. This object refers to the hardware implementation of the port. It will be 'embedded' if the hardware equivalent to Gigabit interface card (GBIC) is part of the line card and is unremovable. It will be 'glm' if it's a gigabit link module (GLM). It will be 'gbicSerialId' if the GBIC serial id can be read, else it will be 'gbicNoSerialId'. It will be 'sfpSerialId', if the small form factor (SFP) pluggable GBICs serial id can be read, else it will be 'sfpNoSerialId'.

cfcmPortSerialNumber.name: cfcmPortSerialNumber
cfcmPortSerialNumber.description: The serial number associated with the port (e.g., for a GBIC). If not applicable, the object's value is a zero- length string.

cfcmPortPhysicalNumber.name: cfcmPortPhysicalNumber
cfcmPortPhysicalNumber.description: This is the port's 'Physical Port Number' as defined by GS-3.

cfcmPortAdminSpeed.name: cfcmPortAdminSpeed
cfcmPortAdminSpeed.description: The speed of the interface: 'auto' - auto-negotiation 'tenGbs' - 10Gbs 'fourGbs' - 4Gbs 'twoGbs' - 2Gbs 'oneGbs' - 1Gbs 'halfGbs' - 500Mbs 'quarterGbs' - 250Mbs 'eighthGbs' - 125Mbs

cfcmPortCapProtocols.name: cfcmPortCapProtocols
cfcmPortCapProtocols.description: A bit mask specifying the higher level protocols which are supported on this port. Note that for generic Fx_Ports, E_Ports and B_Ports, this object will indicate all protocols.

cfcmPortOperProtocols.name: cfcmPortOperProtocols
cfcmPortOperProtocols.description: A bit mask specifying the higher level protocols which are currently operational on this port. For Fx_Ports, E_Ports and B_Ports, this object will typically have the value 'unknown'.

cfcmPortStatsTable.name: cfcmPortStatsTable
cfcmPortStatsTable.description: A list of statistics for Fibre Channel ports.

cfcmPortStatsEntry.name: cfcmPortStatsEntry
cfcmPortStatsEntry.description: An entry containing statistics for a Fibre Channel port.

cfcmPortBBCreditZeros.name: cfcmPortBBCreditZeros
cfcmPortBBCreditZeros.description: The number of transitions in/out of the buffer-to-buffer credit zero state. The other side is not providing any credit.

cfcmPortFullInputBuffers.name: cfcmPortFullInputBuffers
cfcmPortFullInputBuffers.description: The number of occurrences when all input buffers of a port were full and outbound buffer-to-buffer credit transitioned to zero, i.e., there became no credit to provide to other side.

cfcmPortClass2RxFrames.name: cfcmPortClass2RxFrames
cfcmPortClass2RxFrames.description: The number of Class 2 frames received at this port.

cfcmPortClass2RxOctets.name: cfcmPortClass2RxOctets
cfcmPortClass2RxOctets.description: The number of octets contained in Class 2 frames received at this port.

cfcmPortClass2TxFrames.name: cfcmPortClass2TxFrames
cfcmPortClass2TxFrames.description: The number of Class 2 frames transmitted out of this port.

cfcmPortClass2TxOctets.name: cfcmPortClass2TxOctets
cfcmPortClass2TxOctets.description: The number of octets contained in Class 2 frames transmitted out of this port.

cfcmPortClass2Discards.name: cfcmPortClass2Discards
cfcmPortClass2Discards.description: The number of Class 2 frames that were discarded upon reception at this port.

cfcmPortClass2RxFbsyFrames.name: cfcmPortClass2RxFbsyFrames
cfcmPortClass2RxFbsyFrames.description: The number of times that F_BSY was returned to this port as a result of a Class 2 frame that could not be delivered to the other end of the link. This can occur when either the fabric or the destination port is temporarily busy. Note that this counter will never increment for an F_Port.

cfcmPortClass2RxPbsyFrames.name: cfcmPortClass2RxPbsyFrames
cfcmPortClass2RxPbsyFrames.description: The number of times that P_BSY was returned to this port as a result of a Class 2 frame that could not be delivered to the other end of the link. This can occur when the destination port is temporarily busy.

cfcmPortClass2RxFrjtFrames.name: cfcmPortClass2RxFrjtFrames
cfcmPortClass2RxFrjtFrames.description: The number of times that F_RJT was returned to this port as a result of a Class 2 frame that was rejected by the fabric. Note that this counter will never increment for an F_Port.

cfcmPortClass2RxPrjtFrames.name: cfcmPortClass2RxPrjtFrames
cfcmPortClass2RxPrjtFrames.description: The number of times that P_RJT was returned to this port as a result of a Class 2 frame that was rejected at the destination N_Port.

cfcmPortClass2TxFbsyFrames.name: cfcmPortClass2TxFbsyFrames
cfcmPortClass2TxFbsyFrames.description: The number of times that F_BSY was generated by this port as a result of a Class 2 frame that could not be delivered because either the Fabric or the destination port was temporarily busy. Note that this counter will never increment for an N_Port.

cfcmPortClass2TxPbsyFrames.name: cfcmPortClass2TxPbsyFrames
cfcmPortClass2TxPbsyFrames.description: The number of times that P_BSY was generated by this port as a result of a Class 2 frame that could not be delivered because the destination port was temporarily busy. Note that this counter will never increment for an F_Port.

cfcmPortClass2TxFrjtFrames.name: cfcmPortClass2TxFrjtFrames
cfcmPortClass2TxFrjtFrames.description: The number of times that F_RJT was generated by this port as a result of a Class 2 frame being rejected by the fabric. Note that this counter will never increment for an N_Port.

cfcmPortClass2TxPrjtFrames.name: cfcmPortClass2TxPrjtFrames
cfcmPortClass2TxPrjtFrames.description: The number of times that P_RJT was generated by this port as a result of a Class 2 frame being rejected at the destination N_Port. Note that this counter will never increment for an F_Port.

cfcmPortClass3RxFrames.name: cfcmPortClass3RxFrames
cfcmPortClass3RxFrames.description: The number of Class 3 frames received at this port.

cfcmPortClass3RxOctets.name: cfcmPortClass3RxOctets
cfcmPortClass3RxOctets.description: The number of octets contained in Class 3 frames received at this port.

cfcmPortClass3TxFrames.name: cfcmPortClass3TxFrames
cfcmPortClass3TxFrames.description: The number of Class 3 frames transmitted out of this port.

cfcmPortClass3TxOctets.name: cfcmPortClass3TxOctets
cfcmPortClass3TxOctets.description: The number of octets contained in Class 3 frames transmitted out of this port.

cfcmPortClass3Discards.name: cfcmPortClass3Discards
cfcmPortClass3Discards.description: The number of Class 3 frames that were discarded upon reception at this port.

cfcmPortClassFRxFrames.name: cfcmPortClassFRxFrames
cfcmPortClassFRxFrames.description: The number of Class F frames received at this port.

cfcmPortClassFRxOctets.name: cfcmPortClassFRxOctets
cfcmPortClassFRxOctets.description: The number of octets contained in Class F frames received at this port.

cfcmPortClassFTxFrames.name: cfcmPortClassFTxFrames
cfcmPortClassFTxFrames.description: The number of Class F frames transmitted out of this port.

cfcmPortClassFTxOctets.name: cfcmPortClassFTxOctets
cfcmPortClassFTxOctets.description: The number of octets contained in Class F frames transmitted out of this port.

cfcmPortClassFDiscards.name: cfcmPortClassFDiscards
cfcmPortClassFDiscards.description: The number of Class F frames that were discarded upon reception at this port.

cfcmPortLcStatsTable.name: cfcmPortLcStatsTable
cfcmPortLcStatsTable.description: A list of Counter32-based statistics which are a shadow of the Counter64 statistics in the cfcmPortStatsTable, for systems which do not support Counter64.

cfcmPortLcStatsEntry.name: cfcmPortLcStatsEntry
cfcmPortLcStatsEntry.description: An entry containing low-capacity (i.e., based on Counter32) statistics for a Fibre Channel port.

cfcmPortLcBBCreditZeros.name: cfcmPortLcBBCreditZeros
cfcmPortLcBBCreditZeros.description: The number of transitions in/out of the buffer-to-buffer credit zero state. The other side is not providing any credit.

cfcmPortLcFullInputBuffers.name: cfcmPortLcFullInputBuffers
cfcmPortLcFullInputBuffers.description: The number of occurrences when all input buffers of a port were full and outbound buffer-to-buffer credit transitioned to zero, i.e., there became no credit to provide to other side.

cfcmPortLcClass2RxFrames.name: cfcmPortLcClass2RxFrames
cfcmPortLcClass2RxFrames.description: The number of Class 2 frames received at this port.

cfcmPortLcClass2RxOctets.name: cfcmPortLcClass2RxOctets
cfcmPortLcClass2RxOctets.description: The number of octets contained in Class 2 frames received at this port.

cfcmPortLcClass2TxFrames.name: cfcmPortLcClass2TxFrames
cfcmPortLcClass2TxFrames.description: The number of Class 2 frames transmitted out of this port.

cfcmPortLcClass2TxOctets.name: cfcmPortLcClass2TxOctets
cfcmPortLcClass2TxOctets.description: The number of octets contained in Class 2 frames transmitted out of this port.

cfcmPortLcClass2Discards.name: cfcmPortLcClass2Discards
cfcmPortLcClass2Discards.description: The number of Class 2 frames that were discarded upon reception at this port.

cfcmPortLcClass2RxFbsyFrames.name: cfcmPortLcClass2RxFbsyFrames
cfcmPortLcClass2RxFbsyFrames.description: The number of times that F_BSY was returned to this port as a result of a Class 2 frame that could not be delivered to the other end of the link. This can occur when either the fabric or the destination port is temporarily busy. Note that this counter will never increment for an F_Port.

cfcmPortLcClass2RxPbsyFrames.name: cfcmPortLcClass2RxPbsyFrames
cfcmPortLcClass2RxPbsyFrames.description: The number of times that P_BSY was returned to this port as a result of a Class 2 frame that could not be delivered to the other end of the link. This can occur when the destination port is temporarily busy.

cfcmPortLcClass2RxFrjtFrames.name: cfcmPortLcClass2RxFrjtFrames
cfcmPortLcClass2RxFrjtFrames.description: The number of times that F_RJT was returned to this port as a result of a Class 2 frame that was rejected by the fabric. Note that this counter will never increment for an F_Port.

cfcmPortLcClass2RxPrjtFrames.name: cfcmPortLcClass2RxPrjtFrames
cfcmPortLcClass2RxPrjtFrames.description: The number of times that P_RJT was returned to this port as a result of a Class 2 frame that was rejected at the destination N_Port.

cfcmPortLcClass2TxFbsyFrames.name: cfcmPortLcClass2TxFbsyFrames
cfcmPortLcClass2TxFbsyFrames.description: The number of times that F_BSY was generated by this port as a result of a Class 2 frame that could not be delivered because either the Fabric or the destination port was temporarily busy. Note that this counter will never increment for an N_Port.

cfcmPortLcClass2TxPbsyFrames.name: cfcmPortLcClass2TxPbsyFrames
cfcmPortLcClass2TxPbsyFrames.description: The number of times that P_BSY was generated by this port as a result of a Class 2 frame that could not be delivered because the destination port was temporarily busy. Note that this counter will never increment for an F_Port.

cfcmPortLcClass2TxFrjtFrames.name: cfcmPortLcClass2TxFrjtFrames
cfcmPortLcClass2TxFrjtFrames.description: The number of times that F_RJT was generated by this port as a result of a Class 2 frame being rejected by the fabric. Note that this counter will never increment for an N_Port.

cfcmPortLcClass2TxPrjtFrames.name: cfcmPortLcClass2TxPrjtFrames
cfcmPortLcClass2TxPrjtFrames.description: The number of times that P_RJT was generated by this port as a result of a Class 2 frame being rejected at the destination N_Port. Note that this counter will never increment for an F_Port.

cfcmPortLcClass3RxFrames.name: cfcmPortLcClass3RxFrames
cfcmPortLcClass3RxFrames.description: The number of Class 3 frames received at this port.

cfcmPortLcClass3RxOctets.name: cfcmPortLcClass3RxOctets
cfcmPortLcClass3RxOctets.description: The number of octets contained in Class 3 frames received at this port.

cfcmPortLcClass3TxFrames.name: cfcmPortLcClass3TxFrames
cfcmPortLcClass3TxFrames.description: The number of Class 3 frames transmitted out of this port.

cfcmPortLcClass3TxOctets.name: cfcmPortLcClass3TxOctets
cfcmPortLcClass3TxOctets.description: The number of octets contained in Class 3 frames transmitted out of this port.

cfcmPortLcClass3Discards.name: cfcmPortLcClass3Discards
cfcmPortLcClass3Discards.description: The number of Class 3 frames that were discarded upon reception at this port.

cfcmPortErrorsTable.name: cfcmPortErrorsTable
cfcmPortErrorsTable.description: Error counters for Fibre Channel ports.

cfcmPortErrorsEntry.name: cfcmPortErrorsEntry
cfcmPortErrorsEntry.description: Error counters for a Fibre Channel port.

cfcmPortRxLinkResets.name: cfcmPortRxLinkResets
cfcmPortRxLinkResets.description: The number of Link resets (LR primitives) received.

cfcmPortTxLinkResets.name: cfcmPortTxLinkResets
cfcmPortTxLinkResets.description: The number of Link resets (LRs primitive) transmitted.

cfcmPortLinkResets.name: cfcmPortLinkResets
cfcmPortLinkResets.description: The number of times the reset link protocol was initiated on this port. This includes the number of Loop Initialization Primitive (LIP) events on an arbitrated loop port.

cfcmPortRxOfflineSequences.name: cfcmPortRxOfflineSequences
cfcmPortRxOfflineSequences.description: The number of Offline Primitive OLS received at this port.

cfcmPortTxOfflineSequences.name: cfcmPortTxOfflineSequences
cfcmPortTxOfflineSequences.description: The number of Offline Primitive OLS transmitted by this port.

cfcmPortLinkFailures.name: cfcmPortLinkFailures
cfcmPortLinkFailures.description: The number of link failures. This count is part of FC-PH's Link Error Status Block (LESB).

cfcmPortLossofSynchs.name: cfcmPortLossofSynchs
cfcmPortLossofSynchs.description: The number of instances of synchronization loss detected at this port. This count is part of FC-PH's Link Error Status Block (LESB).

cfcmPortLossofSignals.name: cfcmPortLossofSignals
cfcmPortLossofSignals.description: The number of instances of signal loss detected at this port. This count is part of FC-PH's Link Error Status Block (LESB).

cfcmPortPrimSeqProtocolErrors.name: cfcmPortPrimSeqProtocolErrors
cfcmPortPrimSeqProtocolErrors.description: The number of primitive sequence protocol errors detected at this port. This count is part of CFC-PH's Link Error Status Block (LESB).

cfcmPortInvalidTxWords.name: cfcmPortInvalidTxWords
cfcmPortInvalidTxWords.description: The number of invalid transmission words received at this port. This count is part of FC-PH's Link Error Status Block (LESB).

cfcmPortInvalidCRCs.name: cfcmPortInvalidCRCs
cfcmPortInvalidCRCs.description: The number of frames received with invalid CRC. This count is part of FC-PH's Link Error Status Block (LESB).

cfcmPortInvalidOrderedSets.name: cfcmPortInvalidOrderedSets
cfcmPortInvalidOrderedSets.description: The number of invalid ordered sets received at this port.

cfcmPortFrameTooLongs.name: cfcmPortFrameTooLongs
cfcmPortFrameTooLongs.description: The number of frames received at this port where the frame length was greater than what was agreed to in FLOGI/PLOGI. This could be caused by losing the end of frame delimiter.

cfcmPortTruncatedFrames.name: cfcmPortTruncatedFrames
cfcmPortTruncatedFrames.description: The number of frames received at this port where the frame length was less than the minimum indicated by the frame header - normally 24 bytes, but it could be more if the DFCTL field indicates an optional header should have been present.

cfcmPortAddressErrors.name: cfcmPortAddressErrors
cfcmPortAddressErrors.description: The number of frames received with unknown addressing. e.x. unknown SID or DID. the SID or DID is not known to the routing algorithm.

cfcmPortDelimiterErrors.name: cfcmPortDelimiterErrors
cfcmPortDelimiterErrors.description: The number of invalid frame delimiters received at this port. An example is a frame with a class 2 start and a class 3 at the end.

cfcmPortEncodingDisparityErrors.name: cfcmPortEncodingDisparityErrors
cfcmPortEncodingDisparityErrors.description: The number of encoding disparity errors received at this port.

cfcmPortOtherErrors.name: cfcmPortOtherErrors
cfcmPortOtherErrors.description: The number of errors which were detected on this port but which were not counted by any other error counter in this row.

cfcmFxPortTable.name: cfcmFxPortTable
cfcmFxPortTable.description: Additional information about Fibre Channel ports which is specific to Fx_Ports. This table will contain one entry for each cfcmPortTable entry which represents an Fx_Port.

cfcmFxPortEntry.name: cfcmFxPortEntry
cfcmFxPortEntry.description: Each entry contains information about FC protocol related timer values of a specific Fx_Port and information about buffer capacity, maximum data field size of frames handled by this port and other capability information.

cfcmFxPortRatov.name: cfcmFxPortRatov
cfcmFxPortRatov.description: The Resource_Allocation_Timeout Value configured for this Fx_Port. This is used as the timeout value for determining when to reuse an Nx_Port resource such as a Recovery_Qualifier. It represents the Error_Detect_Timeout value (see cfcmFxPortEdtov) plus twice the maximum time that a frame may be delayed within the Fabric and still be delivered.

cfcmFxPortEdtov.name: cfcmFxPortEdtov
cfcmFxPortEdtov.description: The Error_Detect_Timeout value configured for this Fx_Port. This is used as the timeout value for detecting an error condition.

cfcmFxPortRttov.name: cfcmFxPortRttov
cfcmFxPortRttov.description: The Receiver_Transmitter_Timeout value of this Fx_Port. This is used by the receiver logic to detect Loss of Synchronization.

cfcmFxPortHoldTime.name: cfcmFxPortHoldTime
cfcmFxPortHoldTime.description: The maximum time that this Fx_Port shall hold a frame before discarding the frame if it is unable to deliver the frame. The value 0 means that this Fx_Port does not support this parameter.

cfcmFxPortCapBbCreditMax.name: cfcmFxPortCapBbCreditMax
cfcmFxPortCapBbCreditMax.description: The maximum number of receive buffers which this port is capable of making available for holding frames from attached Nx_Port(s).

cfcmFxPortCapBbCreditMin.name: cfcmFxPortCapBbCreditMin
cfcmFxPortCapBbCreditMin.description: The minimum number of receive buffers which this port is capable of making available for holding frames from attached Nx_Port(s).

cfcmFxPortCapDataFieldSizeMax.name: cfcmFxPortCapDataFieldSizeMax
cfcmFxPortCapDataFieldSizeMax.description: The maximum size in bytes of the Data Field in a frame that this Fx_Port is capable of receiving from an attached Nx_Port.

cfcmFxPortCapDataFieldSizeMin.name: cfcmFxPortCapDataFieldSizeMin
cfcmFxPortCapDataFieldSizeMin.description: The minimum size in bytes of the Data Field in a frame that this Fx_Port is capable of receiving from an attached Nx_Port.

cfcmFxPortCapClass2SeqDeliv.name: cfcmFxPortCapClass2SeqDeliv
cfcmFxPortCapClass2SeqDeliv.description: An indication of whether this Fx_Port is capable of supporting Class 2 Sequential Delivery.

cfcmFxPortCapClass3SeqDeliv.name: cfcmFxPortCapClass3SeqDeliv
cfcmFxPortCapClass3SeqDeliv.description: An indication of whether this Fx_Port is capable of supporting Class 3 Sequential Delivery.

cfcmFxPortCapHoldTimeMax.name: cfcmFxPortCapHoldTimeMax
cfcmFxPortCapHoldTimeMax.description: The maximum holding time that this Fx_Port is capable of supporting.

cfcmFxPortCapHoldTimeMin.name: cfcmFxPortCapHoldTimeMin
cfcmFxPortCapHoldTimeMin.description: The minimum holding time that this Fx_Port is capable of supporting.

cfcmISPortTable.name: cfcmISPortTable
cfcmISPortTable.description: Additional information about E_Ports, B_Ports, and any other type of Fibre Channel port to which inter-switch links can be connected. This table will contain one entry for each cfcmPortTable entry which represents such a port.

cfcmISPortEntry.name: cfcmISPortEntry
cfcmISPortEntry.description: Each entry contains information about a specific port connected to an inter-switch link.

cfcmISPortClassFCredit.name: cfcmISPortClassFCredit
cfcmISPortClassFCredit.description: The maximum number of Class F data frames which can be transmitted by the inter-switch port without receipt of ACK or Link_Response frames.

cfcmISPortClassFDataFieldSize.name: cfcmISPortClassFDataFieldSize
cfcmISPortClassFDataFieldSize.description: The Receive Data Field Size which the inter-switch port has agreed to support for Class F frames to/from this port. The size specifies the largest Data Field Size for an FT_1 frame.

cfcmFLoginTable.name: cfcmFLoginTable
cfcmFLoginTable.description: A table that contains one entry for each Nx_Port logged- in/attached to a particular Fx_Port in the switch. Each entry contains the services parameters established during the most recent Fabric Login, explicit or implicit. Note that an Fx_Port may have one or more Nx_Ports attached to it.

cfcmFLoginEntry.name: cfcmFLoginEntry
cfcmFLoginEntry.description: An entry containing service parameters established from a successful Fabric Login.

cfcmFLoginNxPortIndex.name: cfcmFLoginNxPortIndex
cfcmFLoginNxPortIndex.description: An arbitrary integer which uniquely identifies an Nx_Port amongst all those attached to the Fx_Port indicated by ifIndex.

cfcmFLoginPortWwn.name: cfcmFLoginPortWwn
cfcmFLoginPortWwn.description: The port name of the attached Nx_Port, or the zero-length string if unknown.

cfcmFLoginNodeWwn.name: cfcmFLoginNodeWwn
cfcmFLoginNodeWwn.description: The node name of the attached Nx_Port, or the zero-length string if unknown.

cfcmFLoginBbCreditModel.name: cfcmFLoginBbCreditModel
cfcmFLoginBbCreditModel.description: The buffer-to-buffer credit model in use by the Fx_Port.

cfcmFLoginBbCredit.name: cfcmFLoginBbCredit
cfcmFLoginBbCredit.description: The number of buffers available for holding frames to be transmitted to the attached Nx_Port. These buffers are for buffer-to-buffer flow control in the direction from Fx_Port to Nx_Port.

cfcmFLoginClassesAgreed.name: cfcmFLoginClassesAgreed
cfcmFLoginClassesAgreed.description: The Classes of Service which the Fx_Port has agreed to support for this Nx_Port.

cfcmFLoginClass2SeqDelivAgreed.name: cfcmFLoginClass2SeqDelivAgreed
cfcmFLoginClass2SeqDelivAgreed.description: An indication of whether the Fx_Port has agreed to support Class 2 sequential delivery for this Nx_Port. This is only meaningful if Class 2 service has been agreed.

cfcmFLoginClass2DataFieldSize.name: cfcmFLoginClass2DataFieldSize
cfcmFLoginClass2DataFieldSize.description: The Receive Data Field Size which the Fx_Port has agreed to support for Class 2 frames to/from this Nx_Port. The size specifies the largest Data Field Size for an FT_1 frame. This is only meaningful if Class 2 service has been agreed.

cfcmFLoginClass3SeqDelivAgreed.name: cfcmFLoginClass3SeqDelivAgreed
cfcmFLoginClass3SeqDelivAgreed.description: An indication of whether the Fx_Port has agreed to support Class 3 sequential delivery for this Nx_Port. This is only meaningful if Class 3 service has been agreed.

cfcmFLoginClass3DataFieldSize.name: cfcmFLoginClass3DataFieldSize
cfcmFLoginClass3DataFieldSize.description: The Receive Data Field Size which the Fx_Port has agreed to support for Class 3 frames to/from this Nx_Port. The size specifies the largest Data Field Size for an FT_1 frame. This is only meaningful if Class 3 service has been agreed.

cfcmLinkTable.name: cfcmLinkTable
cfcmLinkTable.description: A table containing any Fibre Channel link information which is known to local Fibre Channel managed instances. One end of such a link is typically at a local port, but the table can also contain information on links for which neither end is a local port. If one end of a link terminates locally, then that end is termed 'end1'; the other end is termed 'end2'.

cfcmLinkEntry.name: cfcmLinkEntry
cfcmLinkEntry.description: An entry containing information which a particular Fibre Channel managed instance has about a Fibre Channel link. The two ends of the link are called 'end1' and 'end2'.

cfcmLinkIndex.name: cfcmLinkIndex
cfcmLinkIndex.description: An arbitrary integer which uniquely identifies one link within the set of links about which a particular managed instance has information.

cfcmLinkEnd1NodeWwn.name: cfcmLinkEnd1NodeWwn
cfcmLinkEnd1NodeWwn.description: The node name of end1, or the zero-length string if unknown.

cfcmLinkEnd1PhysPortNumber.name: cfcmLinkEnd1PhysPortNumber
cfcmLinkEnd1PhysPortNumber.description: The physical port number of end1, or zero if unknown.

cfcmLinkEnd1PortWwn.name: cfcmLinkEnd1PortWwn
cfcmLinkEnd1PortWwn.description: The port WWN of end1, or the zero-length string if unknown. ('end1' is local if this value is equal to the value of cfcmPortWwn in one of the rows of the cfcmPortTable.)

cfcmLinkEnd2NodeWwn.name: cfcmLinkEnd2NodeWwn
cfcmLinkEnd2NodeWwn.description: The node name of end2, or the zero-length string if unknown.

cfcmLinkEnd2PhysPortNumber.name: cfcmLinkEnd2PhysPortNumber
cfcmLinkEnd2PhysPortNumber.description: The physical port number of end2, or zero if unknown.

cfcmLinkEnd2PortWwn.name: cfcmLinkEnd2PortWwn
cfcmLinkEnd2PortWwn.description: The port WWN of end2, or the zero-length string if unknown.

cfcmLinkEnd2AgentAddress.name: cfcmLinkEnd2AgentAddress
cfcmLinkEnd2AgentAddress.description: The address of the SNMP agent for the Fibre Channel Interconnect Element or Platform of which end2 is a part. If the address is unknown, the value of this object is the zero-length string.

cfcmLinkEnd2UnitType.name: cfcmLinkEnd2UnitType
cfcmLinkEnd2UnitType.description: The type of/function(s) performed by the Fibre Channel Interconnect Element or Platform of which end2 is a part.

cfcmLinkEnd2FcAddressId.name: cfcmLinkEnd2FcAddressId
cfcmLinkEnd2FcAddressId.description: The Fibre Channel Address ID of end2, or the zero-length string if unknown.

cfcmgmtCompliance.name: cfcmgmtCompliance
cfcmgmtCompliance.description: Describes the requirements for compliance to this Fibre Channel Management MIB.

cfcmInstanceBasicGroup.name: cfcmInstanceBasicGroup
cfcmInstanceBasicGroup.description: Basic information about Fibre Channel managed instances.

cfcmSwitchBasicGroup.name: cfcmSwitchBasicGroup
cfcmSwitchBasicGroup.description: Basic information about Fibre Channel switches.

cfcmPortBasicGroup.name: cfcmPortBasicGroup
cfcmPortBasicGroup.description: Basic information about Fibre Channel ports.

cfcmPortStatsGroup.name: cfcmPortStatsGroup
cfcmPortStatsGroup.description: Traffic statistics, which are not specific to any one class of service, for Fibre Channel ports.

cfcmPortClass23StatsGroup.name: cfcmPortClass23StatsGroup
cfcmPortClass23StatsGroup.description: Traffic statistics for Class 2 and Class 3 traffic on Fibre Channel ports.

cfcmPortClassFStatsGroup.name: cfcmPortClassFStatsGroup
cfcmPortClassFStatsGroup.description: Traffic statistics for Class F traffic on Fibre Channel ports.

cfcmPortLcStatsGroup.name: cfcmPortLcStatsGroup
cfcmPortLcStatsGroup.description: Low-capacity (32-bit) statistics for Fibre Channel ports.

cfcmPortErrorsGroup.name: cfcmPortErrorsGroup
cfcmPortErrorsGroup.description: Error statistics for Fibre Channel ports.

cfcmSwitchPortGroup.name: cfcmSwitchPortGroup
cfcmSwitchPortGroup.description: Information about ports on a Fibre Channel switch.

cfcmSwitchLoginGroup.name: cfcmSwitchLoginGroup
cfcmSwitchLoginGroup.description: Information known to a Fibre Channel switch about attached/logged-in Nx_Ports.
